More than 100 people demonstrated on Wednesday following the death of a teacher in Isebania, at the border of Kenya and Tanzania.The teacher was killed and one person wounded during a night raid at an M-Pesa shop.Residents of Isebania, at the border of Kenya and Tanzania, during a demonstration over rising cases of insecurity, November 30, 2016. /COURTESYThe protesters barricaded roads by lighting bonfires in the protest over rising cases of insecurity.They engaged in running battles with police who dispersed them by lobbing tear gas canisters.Residents of Isebania, at the border of Kenya and Tanzania, during a demonstration over rising cases of insecurity, November 30, 2016. /COURTESYSome of them hurled stones in retaliation, accusing officers of neglecting their duty to protect citizens.More to follow